                                GraphicDump

        GraphicDump prints exactly what appears on your monitor. To use it
your printer must be capable of printing graphic images, and the settings
in the Printer and PrinterGFX editors must be appropriate for your
printer. The print out will be full width allowed by your printer, unless
you use the Limits setting to specify printout dimensions in the PrinterGFX
editor.

        Double-click on the GraphicDump icon to start the printing process.
There is a ten-second delay which enables you to display the screen, menus,
windows and whatever you wish to print. After the Front most screen is sent
out to the printer.

        You can use sizing Tool Types to determine the size of the
printout. You must ensure that the Limits Type gadget in the PrinterGfx
editor is set to Ignore for these arguments to be recognized.

        SIZE=<xdots>:<ydots> Prints out the screen using the dimensions
specified. For <xdots> substitute the width in printer dots, and for
<ydots> the height.

        SIZE=tiny Prints out the screen at 1/4 the total width allowed by
the printer.

        SIZE=small Prints out the screen at 1/2 the total width allowed by
the printer.

        SIZE=medium Prints out the screen at 3/4 the total width allowed by
the printer.

        SIZE=large Prints out the screen at the total width allowed by
the printer. This is the default setting.



